			<div id="intro">
				<p> Hello! You can find me around the internet or in real life, but this is my story so far. I'm in my first year at Harvard Business School. It was a difficult decision, and here are my<a href="http://blog.ellenchisa.com/2014/04/19/some-news-hbs/"> reasons for going</a>. It's been up and down, and I've been sharing what I've learned along the way <a href="http://blog.ellenchisa.com/category/hbs/"> here</a>. I really miss making things, so I've been working on a side project with<a href="http://www.tmrudick.com"> Tom</a>. We'll announce it soon. By the end of my time at HBS, I want to have started my own company.
			</div>

			<div id="books">
				<p>I'm disappointed that I no longer have as much time to read. Right now I'm reading <a href="{{last_book.link}}">{{last_book.title}}</a> by {{last_book.author}}. My New Year's Resolution was to commit something to Github everyday. I gave up, but I did finish a <a href="http://www.ellenchisa.com/books/">visualization of what I've read so far</a>. You can fork it on Github to make your own. Some other things I enjoy are <a href="http://www.ellenchisa.com/writing">writing</a>, SCUBA Diving, and the Twilight Zone pinball machine.</p>
			</div>

